<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="48" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1665,2001]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1665,1691]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Thorax, abdomen and legs predominantly yellow; postcranium black with gray pruinescence; male tergite 8 with blunt distal forked projection. Female hind tibia with pinnate scales along most of dorsal surface and ventral basal third.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1665,2001]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,152,410]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,352,1781,1807]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[360,471,1782,1808]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Holotype</typeStatus>
male. Frons approximately half anterior ocellus width. Face slightly wider than frons only at ventral margin. Postcranium black. Antenna black with pedicel yellowish. Palpus yellow. Thorax shining yellow with yellow to gray-brown pruinescence. Setae: 4 dorsocentrals; 1 supra-alar presutural; 2 pairs of scutellars; 3-5 antepronotals; 1–3 tiny proepisternals; 3–5 katatergitals. Legs shining yellow with apex of mid and hind femora, apex of hind tibia and all tarsi black, except fore and mid tarsomere 1 mostly yellow and fore tarsomeres 1–3 white distally. Mid tibia with two slightly stout dorsal setae at median third; hind tibia with 4–5 slender dorsal setae; first hind tarsomere with three longer dorsal setae. Wing with costal and apical margin brown infuscated (
<figureCitation box="[484,576,190,216]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,254,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,465,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-203@10.[151,1436,437,1833]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrostomus furcatus, n. sp., paratypes from Amazonas. A–F, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, detail of posterior cercus in alternate view; F, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. G–I, female; G, wing; H, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; I, sternite 8, ventral view; J, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: B–C,H–I = 0.2 mm; D,E,J = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321586" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321586/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Fig. 5a</figureCitation>
). Halter dark yellow to brown. Abdomen shining yellow with black terminalia. Tergite 8 (
<figureCitation box="[438,533,229,255]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,254,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,465,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-203@10.[151,1436,437,1833]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrostomus furcatus, n. sp., paratypes from Amazonas. A–F, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, detail of posterior cercus in alternate view; F, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. G–I, female; G, wing; H, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; I, sternite 8, ventral view; J, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: B–C,H–I = 0.2 mm; D,E,J = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321586" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321586/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Fig. 5b</figureCitation>
) with blunt bifid distal projection. Epandrium with anterodorsal and posterodorsal protuberances of subequal length (
<figureCitation box="[717,802,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,254,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,465,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-203@10.[151,1436,437,1833]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrostomus furcatus, n. sp., paratypes from Amazonas. A–F, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, detail of posterior cercus in alternate view; F, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. G–I, female; G, wing; H, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; I, sternite 8, ventral view; J, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: B–C,H–I = 0.2 mm; D,E,J = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321586" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321586/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Fig. 5c</figureCitation>
). Anterior cercus somewhat elongate; posterior cercus rounded distally, with a few anterodorsal setae and two internal protuberances, one longer and apparently bifid anteriorly and other small and simple posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[734,861,345,371]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,254,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,465,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-203@10.[151,1436,437,1833]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrostomus furcatus, n. sp., paratypes from Amazonas. A–F, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, detail of posterior cercus in alternate view; F, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. G–I, female; G, wing; H, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; I, sternite 8, ventral view; J, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: B–C,H–I = 0.2 mm; D,E,J = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321586" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321586/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Figs. 5d–e</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[1044,1124,345,371]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,254,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,465,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-203@10.[151,1436,437,1833]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrostomus furcatus, n. sp., paratypes from Amazonas. A–F, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, detail of posterior cercus in alternate view; F, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. G–I, female; G, wing; H, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; I, sternite 8, ventral view; J, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: B–C,H–I = 0.2 mm; D,E,J = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321586" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321586/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Fig. 5f</figureCitation>
) with a few setae medially and paired serrated protuberances distally.
</paragraph>
