<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,152,912]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">
Female. Frons slightly wider than anterior ocellus width; face narrower than frons, approximately one third anterior ocellus width. First hind tarsomere with one longer dorsal seta; hind tibia with pinnate scales on most of dorsal surface and ventrally on basal third. Wing wider than in male, more brown infuscated (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1422,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,254,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,465,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-203@10.[151,1436,437,1833]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrostomus furcatus, n. sp., paratypes from Amazonas. A–F, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, detail of posterior cercus in alternate view; F, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. G–I, female; G, wing; H, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; I, sternite 8, ventral view; J, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: B–C,H–I = 0.2 mm; D,E,J = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321586" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321586/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1389,1422,268,294]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" unit="g" value="5.0">5g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). Terminalia black sparsely gray pruinose. Tergite 8 and sternite 8 as in 
<figureCitation box="[995,1119,306,332]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,254,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,465,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-203@10.[151,1436,437,1833]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrostomus furcatus, n. sp., paratypes from Amazonas. A–F, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, detail of posterior cercus in alternate view; F, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. G–I, female; G, wing; H, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; I, sternite 8, ventral view; J, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: B–C,H–I = 0.2 mm; D,E,J = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321586" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321586/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Figs. 5h–i</figureCitation>
